When practice, sleep, shock, prayer, or exhaustion leaves a blank, do not rush to make it a verdict. Ask what helped you enter it, what can correct your first story, and how you return to work, rest, repair, and care. A silence that makes you steadier and less owned by performance may be useful. A silence that makes you certain, superior, ashamed, or isolated should be handled with help.

